If you are coming from Spring Boot, you are used to H2. You add one dependency, set the profile to test, and your repository tests run in a few milliseconds without Docker. It feels great until the day you push a query that works on H2 and breaks in production on PostgreSQL.
The usual culprit is JSONB. H2 in PostgreSQL compatibility mode covers most of the basic SQL, but it does not really speak PostgreSQL. It does not understand the jsonb operators, native @> containment, or jsonb_path_query. So your green test suite tells you the code works, and staging tells you the truth two hours later.
This post replaces H2 with a real PostgreSQL 17 container using Testcontainers and @ServiceConnection. We will write a repository test that actually exercises JSONB, then make the containers fast enough that you stop missing H2.
